OL,3,CBritney Spears avoids jail after
OL,4,Cpleading guilty to lesser DUI charge
OL,6,FBritney Spears pleaded guilty via her
OL,7,Flawyer to a lesser charge, which means
OL,8,Fshe avoids jail time after California
OL,9,Fprosecutors accused her of driving
OL,10,Funder the influence of alcohol and
OL,11,Fdrugs.
OL,13,FThe 44-year-old pop star, who recently
OL,14,Fcompleted a stint at a rehabilitation
OL,15,Ffacility, didn't appear in Ventura
OL,16,FCounty court.
OL,18,FBut her lawyer, Michael A. Goldstein,
OL,19,Fpleaded guilty on her behalf to what's
OL,20,Fcommonly called a "wet reckless."
OL,26,@|D@SOU|D@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
