PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1777978996
OL,3,CBritney Spears avoids jail after
OL,4,Cpleading guilty to lesser DUI charge
OL,6,F"We appreciate the district attorney
OL,7,Frecognising the positive steps that
OL,8,FBritney is taking to help herself."
OL,10,FGoldstein said Spears returned home
OL,11,Fafter recently completing her rehab
OL,12,Fstint, and that reports that she left
OL,13,Fearly were "absolutely false." Asked
OL,14,Fwhat's next for her, he replied, "I
OL,15,Fdon't know, I'm sure a lot."
OL,17,FDuring the brief hearing, Spears
OL,18,Freceived summary probation, which is
OL,19,Finformal and doesn't involve mandatory
OL,20,Fmeetings with a parole officer.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@cO]uD@LOUuD@^O]vD@bOUwD@\O]
