OL,3,CBritney Spears avoids jail after
OL,4,Cpleading guilty to lesser DUI charge
OL,6,FDistrict Attorney Erik Nasarenko said
OL,7,Fafter the hearing that Spears had
OL,8,Ftaken "full responsibility," but he
OL,9,Femphasised that DUI is a "serious
OL,10,Fcrime" and said it was essential that
OL,11,Fshe follow the requirements agreed to
OL,12,Fin court, which include continued
OL,13,Fsubstance abuse treatment, weekly
OL,14,Fvisits with a therapist and monthly
OL,15,Fvisits with a psychiatrist.
OL,17,F"We do not want Miss Spears to
OL,18,Freoffend," Nasarenko said.
